          <div class="payout-value">90%</div>
          <div class="payout-label">Maximum Profit Split</div>
          <p>Reach 90% through the scaling plan with consistent profitability.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="payout-card">
          <div class="payout-value">14 Days</div>
          <div class="payout-label">Payout Frequency</div>
          <p>Request withdrawals every 14 days after your first month.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="payout-methods">
        <h3 class="heading-3">Withdrawal Methods</h3>
        <div class="methods-grid">
          <div class="method-item">
            <span class="method-icon">üè¶</span>
            <span class="method-name">Bank Transfer</span>
          </div>
          <div class="method-item">
            <span class="method-icon">üí≥</span>
            <span class="method-name">Skrill</span>
          </div>
          <div class="method-item">
            <span class="method-icon">‚Çø</span>
            <span class="method-name">Crypto (BTC)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <AnalystNotes
        title="FTMO Scaling Plan Explained"
        icon="üìà"
        id="payout-notes"
        variant="dark"
      >
        <h4>How to Grow to $400K and 90% Profit Split</h4>
        <p>FTMO's scaling plan rewards consistent profitability. Here's exactly how to maximize your funded account over time.</p>

        <h5>Scaling Requirements</h5>
        <p>To scale your account, you must achieve a 10% profit over a 4-month period while maintaining profitability for at least 2 of those months. When you meet these criteria, your account doubles in size (up to the $400K maximum).</p>

        <h5>Profit Split Progression</h5>
        <p>Your profit split increases alongside account scaling:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Initial:</strong> 80% profit split</li>
          <li><strong>First scale:</strong> 85% profit split</li>
          <li><strong>Second scale:</strong> 90% profit split (maximum)</li>
        </ul>

        <h5>Real Example</h5>
        <p>Start with a $100K account at 80% split. Over 4 months, make 12% profit ($12,000). You keep $9,600 (80%). After scaling: $200K account at 85% split. Same 12% performance now yields $24,000 profit, you keep $20,400. After second scale: $400K at 90% - 12% is $48,000, you keep $43,200.</p>

        <h5>The Long Game</h5>
        <p>Many traders rush to maximize profits in month one, blow the account, and restart. The smarter approach: treat the first year as account-building. Consistent 2-3% monthly returns compound into significant scaling. A $100K account at 90% split making 3%/month is $32,400/year in take-home - from a $540 initial investment.</p>
      </AnalystNotes>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PLATFORMS SECTION -->
  <section id="platforms" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="heading-2">Trading Platforms</h2>
      <p class="body-large">
        FTMO supports all major trading platforms. Choose the one that fits your trading style and strategy.
      </p>

      <div class="platforms-grid">
        {firm.platforms.map((platform) => (
          <div class="platform-card">
            <h3 class="platform-name">{platform}</h3>
            <div class="platform-status">
              <span class="status-dot"></span>
              Supported
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="instruments-section">
        <h3 class="heading-3">Tradeable Instruments</h3>
        <div class="instruments-grid">
          {firm.instruments.map((instrument) => (
            <div class="instrument-chip">{instrument}</div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <AnalystNotes
        title="Platform Recommendations for FTMO Traders"
        icon="üíª"
        id="platform-notes"
        variant="light"
      >
        <h4>Choosing the Right Platform</h4>
        <p>The platform you choose affects execution speed, available tools, and your overall trading experience. Here's how to decide.</p>

        <h5>MetaTrader 4 - The Industry Standard</h5>
